The paper discusses the value alignment problem of artificial intelligence, which falls under the category of AI safety. The proposed systematic effort to identify and replicate key findings in neuropsychology and allied fields suggests a focus on neural networks and machine learning, which are covered by the sub-categories of cs.NE and cs.LG. The paper also emphasizes the importance of human values, which could be related to the sub-category of cs.HC (human-computer interaction). Finally, the mention of establishing robust foundations for AI safety suggests a potential connection to the sub-category of cs.CYBER (cybersecurity).
